<p style="text-align:justify;">July</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Christian but his principles <span class="AddHand-author">as well</span> as I could discover are not of the best<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  He seems to have acquired the vices of the Indians in addition to his own<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Soon after our arrival the Village was put in an uproar by the unexpected appearance of Six <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Panies</span> who came upon an Embassy to treat of Peace.  This Nation resides about Sixty leaugues below the Mandanes<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">It would appear that last spring some of this nation had accompanied a war party of Sceoux who visited this quarter and killed five of the Natives<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The Mandanes Soon after returned the visit and killed two of their people and gave information that next fall a more formidable visit would be paid as all the Mandane villages would join in the expedition with a view to exterminate the <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Panie</span> Nation.  This declaration was alarming and occasioned the present application in order to avert the Storm<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">A messenger was immediately dispatched to the upper Villages to announce the new arrivals.  In the mean time the Strangers were Entertained with great hospitality.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Not many years ago the <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Panies</span> and Mandanes were in a State of alliance and</p>
